Reasoning: The problem of Minimum Common String Partition is a combinatorial optimization problem that involves strings and their rearrangements. This problem can be studied in the context of computational biology, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of fixed-parameter algorithms suggests that it could belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-categories. Finally, the evaluation of the algorithm on bacteria genomes and synthetic data suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category.
